headline: MACOM to Manufacture HRL’s 40nm GaN-on-SiC Process
summary: LOWELL, Mass., Nov. 04, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- MACOM Technology Solutions Inc. (“MACOM”), a leading supplier of semiconductor products, today announced that it has entered into an agreement with HRL Laboratories (“HRL”) to license and manufacture HRL’s proprietary 40nm T3L GaN-on-silicon carbide (“GaN-on-SiC”) process technology. headline: Is GM Still a Bargain After a 32.8% Price Surge in 2025?
summary: Ever wondered if General Motors stock is actually a bargain or if the recent price surge has left it overvalued? You are not alone, and that is exactly what we are diving into here. General Motors shares have raced ahead, climbing 32.8% year-to-date and notching an 81.1% gain over the last five years, despite a slight dip of 1.7% over the past week.
